issue_body:
Pint is an awesome package, perhaps not popular enough to be on https://github.com/vinta/awesome-python or Anaconda. 

I have a special request that would make Pint very useful for my needs. I work with motion control applications and our electronics carry units like position, current, voltage, force and velocity. 

Communication with our electronics is made through low-level registers that use internal units that can be later converted to SI units using a conversion factor.

This conversion factor depends on some settings such as the resolution of the position sensor or the type of actuator used. It can be dynamically modified if the setting is changed by the user. 

I would like to use Pint to take care of all these units unfortunately there is no way I can work with different registry together neither update the units definition at runtime. 

To summary, I would to be able to do this:

```
class Device(object):
    _conv_factor = {}

    def __init__(self): 
        self.ureg = RegistryBuilder(self._conv_factors)

    @property
    def position(self):
        return self._internal_position * self.ureg.u

    @property
    def current(self):
        return self._internal_current * self.ureg.v

class DeviceA(Device):
    _conv_factors = {'u': '0.00123 meters', 'v': '12.0 amperes'}

class DeviceB(Device):
    _conv_factors = {'u': '0.00123 meters', 'v': '6.0 amperes'}

a = DeviceA()
b = DeviceB()

a.position + b.position # Valid because they both carry the same conversion unit
a.current + b.current # Invalid because the internal conversion factor differ
```

How much work would be required to support this kind of features which can make all the difference in my application?

