I am trying to setup GraphQL / Relay with Django. My goal is that a ReactJS app can use Relay to get data from my Django server. I was able to setup django-graphiql and I can use the web-editor to execute GraphQL queries, so far, so good.

I think I'm failing to setup my Webpack config properly. I added this to my loaders:

```
{
    test: /\.jsx?$/,
    exclude: /node_modules/,
    loaders: ['react-hot', 'babel?stage=0&plugins[]=' + path.join(__dirname, 'babelRelayPlugin')],
  }
)
```

and this is my babelRelayPlugin:

```
var babelRelayPlugin   = require('babel-relay-plugin');
var introspectionQuery = require('graphql/utilities').introspectionQuery;
var request            = require('sync-request');

var graphqlUrl = 'http://localhost:8000/graphql';
var response = request('GET', graphqlUrl, {
  qs: {
    query: introspectionQuery
  }
});

var schema = JSON.parse(response.body.toString('utf-8'));

module.exports = babelRelayPlugin(schema.data, {
  abortOnError: true,
});
```

